Arctic nations have renewed calls for the world to address climate warming. JOHANNESBURG - Arctic nations have renewed calls for the world to address climate warming, but US Secretary of State Rex Tillerson says the United States will not rush to make a decision on its policies.Tillerson was speaking in Alaska, at a meeting of the Arctic Council, which is an advisory group made up of the eight arctic nations and indigenous groups.The council adopted a nine-page declaration, which notes that the arctic is warming at more than twice the rate of the global average.Tillerson signed the document.But in his opening remarks, he cautioned that America is reviewing several important policies, including how the Trump administration will approach the issue of climate change.